# 5 Most Important Requirements
1. Players can open limited lootboxes to get stoves.  
2. Players can trade items with each other.  
3. The game shows price history for every stove.  
4. The game keeps an ownership history.  
5. Players can chat safely to discuss trades.

---

# User Stories

### Lootbox
As a player, I want to open lootboxes so I can get new stoves.

### Trading
As a player, I want to trade items with others so I can improve my collection.

### Price History
As a player, I want to see price history so I can make better trading decisions.

### Ownership History
As a collector, I want to see previous owners so I know how rare an item is.

### Chat
As a player, I want to chat safely so I can negotiate trades.

---

# Functional Requirements (What the game must do)
- The game must let players open lootboxes.  
- The game must allow trading between players.  
- The game must show item price history.  
- The game must track ownership.  
- The game must provide a chat system.

---

# Non-Functional Requirements (How the game should behave)

### Usability
- **User view:** Easy to use and understand.  
- **Developer view:** Clean, simple UI design.

### Performance
- **User view:** Fast actions, no long waiting times.  
- **Developer view:** Server responses should be quick.

### Reliability
- **User view:** Trades must always work correctly.  
- **Developer view:** Use safe database operations.

### Security
- **User view:** Safe chat, no scams.  
- **Developer view:** Validate all inputs and protect user data.

### Scalability
- **User view:** Game works even with many players.  
- **Developer view:** Backend must handle more traffic as needed.
